This paper deals with machine learning and prediction, which are core topics in computer science. The paper specifically focuses on anytime linear prediction, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper also discusses algorithms and their theoretical guarantees, which are topics commonly found in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of feature groups and costs suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the evaluation of the algorithms on real-world datasets suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
